From 1e47bf77d691d4483d438e27758d4a6989883a6e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Tue, 19 May 2026 17:30:14 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 121/174] mm/userfaultfd: mfill_atomic copies one MMUPAGE per
 iteration, not one PAGE
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

mfill_atomic drives UFFDIO_COPY / UFFDIO_ZEROPAGE / UFFDIO_CONTINUE,
calling mfill_atomic_pte once per inner loop iteration and advancing
state.dst_addr / state.src_addr / copied by PAGE_SIZE each time.
mfill_copy_folio_locked / mfill_copy_folio_retry copy PAGE_SIZE bytes
from the userspace src.

Under PGCL (CONFIG_PAGE_MMUSHIFT > 0):
  - The userspace page size (sysconf(_SC_PAGESIZE)) is MMUPAGE_SIZE.
  - validate_range in fs/userfaultfd.c (commit 01acec0521b4) now
    accepts MMUPAGE-aligned uffd ranges, so userspace can call
    UFFDIO_COPY with src=malloc(MMUPAGE_SIZE), len=MMUPAGE_SIZE.
  - mfill_atomic_install_pte then installs one MMUPAGE PTE per call
    (set_pte_at writes a single PTE on PGCL too).
  - But mfill_copy_folio_locked still copies PAGE_SIZE bytes from
    the user-supplied src buffer, reading PAGE_MMUCOUNT MMUPAGES
    past the end of src and returning -EFAULT.  And the outer loop
    advances by PAGE_SIZE while only one MMUPAGE has been mapped.

Visible in the LTP mkdirty test's UFFDIO_COPY subtest on
s390x PGCL=4 (CONFIG_USERFAULTFD=y):

    not ok 3 UFFDIO_COPY failed

Fix: each mfill_atomic iteration handles exactly one MMUPAGE.  Copy
MMUPAGE_SIZE bytes from src into the folio's first sub-page, install
one PTE via mfill_atomic_install_pte (which already operates on a
single PTE = one MMUPAGE), and advance addresses by MMUPAGE_SIZE.
The folio itself is still PAGE_SIZE-allocated; remaining sub-pages
stay unmapped (a small over-allocation for the sub-PAGE-aligned uffd
path, no correctness impact).

At CONFIG_PAGE_MMUSHIFT == 0 MMUPAGE_SIZE == PAGE_SIZE and behaviour
is byte-for-byte unchanged.

Verified: s390x PGCL=4 LTP mkdirty UFFDIO_COPY subtest:

    not ok 3 UFFDIO_COPY failed
    ↓
    ok 3 SIGSEGV generated, page not modified

Remaining mkdirty "not ok 1 write() failed" is a separate PTRACE
write-access subtest failure (follow-up).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 mm/userfaultfd.c | 10 +++++-----
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/mm/userfaultfd.c b/mm/userfaultfd.c
index 5dcf0743d9d2..19106bb7a5cc 100644
--- a/mm/userfaultfd.c
+++ b/mm/userfaultfd.c
@@ -434,7 +434,7 @@ static int mfill_copy_folio_locked(struct folio *folio, unsigned long src_addr)
 	 */
 	pagefault_disable();
 	ret = copy_from_user(kaddr, (const void __user *) src_addr,
-			     PAGE_SIZE);
+			     MMUPAGE_SIZE);
 	pagefault_enable();
 	kunmap_local(kaddr);
 
@@ -521,7 +521,7 @@ static int mfill_copy_folio_retry(struct mfill_state *mfill_state,
 	mfill_put_vma(mfill_state);
 
 	kaddr = kmap_local_folio(folio, 0);
-	err = copy_from_user(kaddr, (const void __user *) src_addr, PAGE_SIZE);
+	err = copy_from_user(kaddr, (const void __user *) src_addr, MMUPAGE_SIZE);
 	kunmap_local(kaddr);
 	if (unlikely(err))
 		return -EFAULT;
@@ -999,9 +999,9 @@ static __always_inline ssize_t mfill_atomic(struct userfaultfd_ctx *ctx,
 		cond_resched();
 
 		if (!err) {
-			state.dst_addr += PAGE_SIZE;
-			state.src_addr += PAGE_SIZE;
-			copied += PAGE_SIZE;
+			state.dst_addr += MMUPAGE_SIZE;
+			state.src_addr += MMUPAGE_SIZE;
+			copied += MMUPAGE_SIZE;
 
 			if (fatal_signal_pending(current))
 				err = -EINTR;
